 build args\n38:   - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n39:   - File: `Makefile`\n40:   - Verify: Image builds with correct tags\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T1.5** Create docker-build-router target\n43:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-build-router`\n44:   - Build with `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router`\n45:   - Pass `VERSION` and `COMMIT_SHA` as build args\n46:   - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n47:   - File: `Makefile`\n48:   - Verify: Image builds with correct tags\n49: \n50: - [ ] **T1.6** Create docker-build-picod target\n51:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-build-picod`\n52:   - Build with `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n53:   - Pass `VERSION` and `COMMIT_SHA` as build args\n54:   - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n55:   - File: `Makefile`\n56:   - Verify: Image builds with correct tags\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## Phase 2: Docker Push Targets\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T2.1** Create docker-push-all aggregate target\n63:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-push-all`\n64:   - Set dependency on all three push targets\n65:   - Add success message\n66:   - File: `Makefile`\n67:   - Verify: `make docker-push-all` pushes all images\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T2.2** Create docker-push-workloadmanager target\n70:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-push-workloadmanager`\n71:   - Push all three tags: `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n72:   - File: `Makefile`\n73:   - Verify: All tags pushed to registry\n74: \n75: - [ ] **T2.3** Create docker-push-router target\n76:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-push-router`\n77:   - Push all three tags: `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n78:   - File: `Makefile`\n79:   - Verify: All tags pushed to registry\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T2.4** Create docker-push-picod target\n82:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-push-picod`\n83:   - Push all three tags: `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n84:   - File: `Makefile`\n85:   - Verify: All tags pushed to registry\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Phase 3: Kind Cluster Integration Targets\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T3.1** Create kind-load-all aggregate target\n92:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-all`\n93:   - Set dependency on all three load targets\n94:   - Add success message\n95:   - File: `Makefile`\n96:   - Verify: `make kind-load-all` loads all images\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.2** Create kind-load-workloadmanager target\n99:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-workloadmanager`\n100:   - Run `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)`\n101:   - File: `Makefile`\n102:   - Verify: Image loaded to Kind cluster\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T3.3** Create kind-load-router target\n105:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-router`\n106:   - Run `kind load docker-image $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)`\n107:   - File: `Makefile`\n108:   - Verify: Image loaded to Kind cluster\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.4** Create kind-load-picod target\n111:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-picod`\n112:   - Run `kind load docker-image $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)`\n113:   - File: `Makefile`\n114:   - Verify: Image loaded to Kind cluster\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Phase 4: Multi-Architecture Build Targets\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.1** Create docker-buildx-all aggregate target\n121:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-all`\n122:   - Set dependency on all three buildx targets\n123:   - Add success message\n124:   - File: `Makefile`\n125:   - Verify: `make docker-buildx-all` builds all multi-arch images\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T4.2** Create docker-buildx-workloadmanager target\n128:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-workloadmanager`\n129:   - Build with `--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n130:   - Use `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile`\n131:   - Add `--push` flag\n132:   - File: `Makefile`\n133:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T4.3** Create docker-buildx-router target\n136:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-router`\n137:   - Build with `--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n138:   - Use `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router`\n139:   - Add `--push` flag\n140:   - File: `Makefile`\n141:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T4.4** Create docker-buildx-picod target\n144:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-picod`\n145:   - Build with `--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n146:   - Use `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n147:   - Add `--push` flag\n148:   - File: `Makefile`\n149:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Phase 5: Cleanup Target\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T5.1** Create docker-clean target\n156:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-clean`\n157:   - Remove all three images with all tags\n158:   - Use `-` prefix on docker rmi commands to ignore errors\n159:   - Use `|| true` for graceful failure\n160:   - File: `Makefile`\n161:   - Verify: `make docker-clean` removes images safely\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Phase 6: Validation Targets\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T6.1** Create docker-validate aggregate target\n168:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate`\n169:   - Set dependency on all three validate targets\n170:   - Add success message\n171:   - File: `Makefile`\n172:   - Verify: `make docker-validate` validates all images\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T6.2** Create docker-validate-workloadmanager target\n175:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate-workloadmanager`\n176:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n177:   - File: `Makefile`\n178:   - Verify: Validation script executed\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T6.3** Create docker-validate-router target\n181:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate-router`\n182:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n183:   - File: `Makefile`\n184:   - Verify: Validation script executed\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T6.4** Create docker-validate-picod target\n187:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate-picod`\n188:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n189:   - File: `Makefile`\n190:   - Verify: Validation script executed\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Phase 7: Test Targets\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T7.1** Create docker-test aggregate target\n197:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-test`\n198:   - Set dependency on `docker-test-build` and `docker-test-runtime`\n199:   - Add success message\n200:   - File: `Makefile`\n201:   - Verify: `make docker-test` runs all tests\n202: \n203: - [ ] **T7.2** Create docker-test-build target\n204:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-test-build`\n205:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n206:   - File: `Makefile`\n207:   - Verify: Build tests executed\n208: \n209: - [ ] **T7.3** Create docker-test-runtime target\n210:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-test-runtime`\n211:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n212:   - File: `Makefile`\n213:   - Verify: Runtime tests executed\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ## Phase 8: Help Target\n218: \n219: - [ ] **T8.1** Create help target with build targets documentation\n220:   - Add `.PHONY: help`\n221:   - Print \"AgentCube Docker Makefile\" header\n222:   - Print \"Build targets:\" section with descriptions\n223:   - File: `Makefile`\n224:   - Verify: Help shows build targets\n225: \n226: - [ ] **T8.2** Add push targets documentation to help\n227:   - Print \"Push targets:\" section with descriptions\n228:   - File: `Makefile`\n229:   - Verify: Help shows push targets\n230: \n231: - [ ] **T8.3** Add Kind targets documentation to help\n232:   - Print \"Kind targets:\" section with descriptions\n233:   - File: `Makefile`\n234:   - Verify: Help shows Kind targets\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T8.4** Add multi-arch targets documentation to help\n237:   - Print \"Multi-arch targets:\" section with descriptions\n238:   - File: `Makefile`\n239:   - Verify: Help shows multi-arch targets\n240: \n241: - [ ] **T8.5** Add test & validate targets documentation to help\n242:   - Print \"Test & validate targets:\" section with descriptions\n243:   - File: `Makefile`\n244:   - Verify: Help shows test and validate targets\n245: \n246: - [ ] **T8.6** Add variables documentation to help\n247:   - Print \"Variables:\" section with current values\n248:   - Show `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n249:   - File: `Makefile`\n250:   - Verify: Help shows variable values\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## Phase 9: Makefile Structure & Best Practices\n255: \n256: - [ ] **T9.1** Ensure all targets are declared as .PHONY\n257:   - Add `.PHONY` declaration for all 20+ targets\n258:   - File: `Makefile`\n259:   - Verify: No target conflicts with files\n260: \n261: - [ ] **T9.2** Use consistent indentation with tabs\n262:   - All recipe lines use tab characters (not spaces)\n263:   - File: `Makefile`\n264:   - Verify: Makefile parses correctly\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T9.3** Add echo messages for user feedback\n267:   - Each target prints progress/success messages\n268:   - Use `@echo` for silent execution with output\n269:   - File: `Makefile`\n270:   - Verify: User sees clear progress during execution\n271: \n272: - [ ] **T9.4** Use variable references consistently\n273:   - Reference images via `$(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE)` not hardcoded\n274:   - Reference tags via `$(DOCKER_TAG)` not hardcoded\n275:   - File: `Makefile`\n276:   - Verify: All image/tag references use variables\n277: \n278: - [ ] **T9.5** Organize targets in logical order\n279:   - Group: Variables → Build → Push → Kind → Buildx → Clean → Validate → Test → Help\n280:   - File: `Makefile`\n281:   - Verify: Related targets are adjacent\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## Phase 10: Make Target Testing\n286: \n287: - [ ] **T10.1** Test docker-build-all target\n288:   - Command: `make docker-build-all`\n289:   - Verify: All three images build successfully\n290:   - Verify: Images tagged with `latest`\n291: \n292: - [ ] **T10.2** Test with custom DOCKER_TAG\n293:   - Command: `make docker-build-all DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0`\n294:   - Verify: Images tagged with `v1.0.0`\n295: \n296: - [ ] **T10.3** Test with custom VERSION\n297:   - Command: `make docker-build-all VERSION=2.0.0`\n298:   - Verify: Images tagged with `2.0.0`\n299: \n300: - [ ] **T10.4** Test docker-clean target\n301:   - Command: `make docker-clean`\n302:   - Verify: Images removed (errors ignored if not present)\n303: \n304: - [ ] **T10.5** Test help target\n305:   - Command: `make help`\n306:   - Verify: All targets documented with correct descriptions\n307:   - Verify: Variable values displayed\n308: \n309: - [ ] **T10.6** Test individual build targets\n310:   - Command: `make docker-build-workloadmanager`\n311:   - Command: `make docker-build-router`\n312:   - Command: `make docker-build-picod`\n313:   - Verify: Each builds independently\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T10.7** Test individual push targets (dry-run or skip if no registry)\n316:   - Verify: Push targets have correct image references\n317:   - Verify: Push targets use all three tags\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## Acceptance Criteria\n322: \n323: 1. ✅ `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` variables defined\n324: 2. ✅ Image name variables for all three components defined\n325: 3. ✅ `docker-build-all` builds all three images sequentially\n326: 4. ✅ Individual build targets for each component exist\n327: 5. ✅ All build targets tag images with DOCKER_TAG, COMMIT_SHA, VERSION\n328: 6. ✅ `docker-push-all` pushes all images to registry\n329: 7. ✅ Individual push targets push all three tags\n330: 8. ✅ `kind-load-all` loads all images to Kind cluster\n331: 9. ✅ Individual kind-load targets exist for each component\n332: 10. ✅ `docker-buildx-all` builds multi-arch images (amd64, arm64)\n333: 11. ✅ Multi-arch build targets use `--push` flag\n334: 12. ✅ `docker-clean` safely removes local images\n335: 13. ✅ `docker-validate` validates all images\n336: 14. ✅ `docker-test` runs build and runtime tests\n337: 15. ✅ `make help` displays all targets with descriptions\n338: 16. ✅ Help shows current variable values\n339: 17. ✅ All targets declared as `.PHONY`\n340: 18. ✅ All recipe lines use tab indentation\n341: 19. ✅ Consistent echo messages for user feedback\n342: 20. ✅ Targets organized in logical groups\n343: 21. ✅ No hardcoded image names or tags in recipes\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: **Notes:**\n348: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (Makefile with full target体系 created)\n349: - Makefile provides complete Docker build/push/test workflow\n350: - Supports single-arch and multi-arch builds\n351: - Integrates with Kind cluster for local testing\n352: - Clean target uses `-` prefix for error tolerance\n353: - Help target provides comprehensive documentation\n354: - All targets are .PHONY to prevent file conflicts\n\n(End of file - total 354 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Tasks\n\n**Module:** root  \n**Language:** Makefile  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Docker Build Targets\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Define Docker configuration variables\n  - Add `DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n  - Add `DOCKER_TAG ?= latest`\n  - Add `VERSION` with git describe fallback\n  - Add `COMMIT_SHA` with git rev-parse fallback\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: All variables defined with correct defaults\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Define image name variables","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775883450771,"end":1775883450817}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775883450846,"sessionID":"ses_28519382affe60QtvVkKG2CIgQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae6f9c3001sEwdKLyWaImpiR","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ae6de92001x4ykdUs7rCRp34","sessionID":"ses_28519382affe60QtvVkKG2CIgQ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":18887,"input":6,"output":244,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":3168,"read":15469}},"cost":0}}
