{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883587738,"sessionID":"ses_28519382affe60QtvVkKG2CIgQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae74111001Erw2TtZtbxd4eq","messageID":"msg_d7ae73132001APuCImqimfUgw7","sessionID":"ses_28519382affe60QtvVkKG2CIgQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_4a03610f741d4a3fa86205b1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md","content":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n\n**Module:** .github  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Repository Structure & Shared Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n  - Directory: `.github/workflows/`\n  - Verify: Directory exists for workflow files\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Define reusable path filter configurations\n  - Create path filter definitions for: `lint`, `coverage`, `python`, `codegen`, `copyright`\n  - Use `dorny/paths-filter` action patterns\n  - Verify: All path filters documented in workflow comments\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Set up environment variable conventions\n  - Document standard env vars: `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n  - Verify: Consistent naming across all workflows\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create `main.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/main.yml`\n  - Name: `Agentcube CI Workflow`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created with correct name\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Define pull_request triggers for main.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Create `build` job in main.yml\n  - Job ID: `build`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined with correct runner\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Add checkout and Docker setup steps\n  - Step: `actions/checkout@v4`\n  - Step: `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3`\n  - Verify: Repository checkout and Buildx setup complete\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Add Docker version verification step\n  - Run: `docker --version` and `docker buildx version`\n  - Verify: Docker and buildx versions logged\n\n- [ ] **T2.6** Add make docker-build execution step\n  - Run: `make docker-build`\n  - Verify: Workload Manager image builds successfully\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: E2E Tests Workflow (e2e.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create `e2e.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/e2e.yml`\n  - Name: `Agentcube E2E Tests`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Define pull_request triggers for e2e.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Create `e2e-test` job in e2e.yml\n  - Job ID: `e2e-test`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Add Go 1.23 setup step\n  - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.23'`\n  - Verify: Go 1.23 installed\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Add Kind cluster installation step\n  - Use: `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`, `version: v0.30.0`, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`\n  - Verify: Kind v0.30.0 installed without cluster creation\n\n- [ ] **T3.6** Set ARTIFACTS_PATH environment variable\n  - Env: `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n  - Verify: Environment variable set for log collection\n\n- [ ] **T3.7** Add make e2e execution step\n  - Run: `make e2e`\n  - Verify: E2E tests execute via run_e2e.sh\n\n- [ ] **T3.8** Add failure log upload step\n  - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with `e2e-logs/` on failure\n  - Condition: `if: failure()`\n  - Verify: Logs uploaded on test failure\n\n- [ ] **T3.9** Add cleanup step with always condition\n  - Run: `make e2e-clean`\n  - Condition: `if: always()`\n  - Verify: Kind cluster cleaned up after tests\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Create `lint.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n  - Name: `Lint`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Define pull_request triggers for lint.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Create `golangci` job in lint.yml\n  - Job ID: `golangci`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T4.4** Add paths-filter for Go code changes\n  - Filter ID: `lint`\n  - Paths: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n  - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n  - Verify: Path filter detects Go-related changes\n\n- [ ] **T4.5** Add conditional Go 1.24 setup\n  - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Go setup only when Go code changes\n\n- [ ] **T4.6** Add make lint execution step\n  - Run: `make lint`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'`\n  - Verify: golangci-lint runs on changed code\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create `python-sdk-tests.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`\n  - Name: `Python SDK Tests`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Define triggers for python-sdk-tests.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`\n  - Verify: Both trigger types configured\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Create `python-sdk-tests` job\n  - Job ID: `python-sdk-tests`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Working directory: `sdk-python`\n  - Verify: Job defined with correct working directory\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Add paths-filter for SDK changes\n  - Filter ID: `sdk`\n  - Paths: `sdk-python/**`\n  - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n  - Verify: Path filter detects SDK changes\n\n- [ ] **T5.5** Add Python 3.12 setup step\n  - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.12'`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Python 3.12 installed in sdk-python directory\n\n- [ ] **T5.6** Add pytest installation step\n  - Run: `pip install pytest`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n  - Verify: pytest installed\n\n- [ ] **T5.7** Add editable package installation step\n  - Run: `pip install -e .`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n  - Verify: SDK installed in editable mode\n\n- [ ] **T5.8** Add pytest execution step\n  - Run: `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n  - Verify: All SDK tests execute\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Create `python-lint.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n  - Name: `Python Lint`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Define pull_request triggers for python-lint.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Create `python_lint` job in python-lint.yml\n  - Job ID: `python_lint`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Add paths-filter for Python code changes\n  - Filter ID: `python`\n  - Paths: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n  - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n  - Verify: Path filter detects Python-related changes\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Add Python 3.10 setup step\n  - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.10'`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Python 3.10 installed\n\n- [ ] **T6.6** Add Ruff installation step\n  - Run: `pip install ruff`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Ruff installed\n\n- [ ] **T6.7** Add Ruff check execution step\n  - Run: `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n  - Working directory: repository root\n  - Verify: Ruff linting runs from repo root\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Create `test-coverage.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml`\n  - Name: `Test Coverage`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Define triggers for test-coverage.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call`\n  - Verify: All three trigger types configured\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Add workflow_call inputs for CODECOV_TOKEN\n  - Input: `CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional, string)\n  - Verify: Token can be passed from reusable workflows\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Create `coverage` job in test-coverage.yml\n  - Job ID: `coverage`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T7.5** Add paths-filter for coverage\n  - Filter ID: `coverage`\n  - Paths: `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n  - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n  - Verify: Path filter excludes non-code files\n\n- [ ] **T7.6** Add free disk space step\n  - Run: Disk cleanup commands for runner\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n  - Verify: More disk space available for Go modules\n\n- [ ] **T7.7** Add Go 1.24 setup step\n  - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Go 1.24 installed\n\n- [ ] **T7.8** Add go test with coverage step\n  - Run: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Coverage report generated\n\n- [ ] **T7.9** Add coverage summary to GitHub step summary\n  - Run: Generate coverage percentage and write to `$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY`\n  - Verify: Coverage displayed in workflow UI\n\n- [ ] **T7.10** Add Codecov upload step\n  - Use: `codecov/codecov-action@v4`\n  - With: `token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}`, `files: coverage.out`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true' && secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN != ''`\n  - Verify: Coverage uploaded to Codecov when token available\n\n- [ ] **T7.11** Add coverage artifact upload step\n  - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with name `go-coverage`, path `coverage.out`\n  - Verify: Coverage file available as artifact\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Create `codegen-check.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml`\n  - Name: `Codegen Check`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Define pull_request triggers for codegen-check.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Create `codegen-check` job in codegen-check.yml\n  - Job ID: `codegen-check`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T8.4** Add paths-filter for codegen changes\n  - Filter ID: `codegen`\n  - Paths: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n  - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n  - Verify: Path filter detects API/codegen changes\n\n- [ ] **T8.5** Add Go 1.24.4 setup step\n  - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24.4'`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.codegen == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Go 1.24.4 installed\n\n- [ ] **T8.6** Add make gen-check execution step\n  - Run: `make gen-check`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.codegen == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Generated code matches committed code\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: Copyright Check Workflow (copyright-check.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T9.1** Create `copyright-check.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml`\n  - Name: `Copyright Check`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T9.2** Define pull_request triggers for copyright-check.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T9.3** Create `build` job in copyright-check.yml\n  - Job ID: `build`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T9.4** Add paths-filter for copyright changes\n  - Filter ID: `copyright`\n  - Paths: All files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n  - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n  - Verify: Path filter detects source code changes\n\n- [ ] **T9.5** Add moreutils installation step\n  - Run: `sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y moreutils`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'`\n  - Verify: `sponge` command available\n\n- [ ] **T9.6** Add make gen-copyright execution step\n  - Run: `make gen-copyright`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'`\n  - Verify: Copyright headers generated\n\n- [ ] **T9.7** Add git diff check step\n  - Run: `git diff --exit-code`\n  - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'`\n  - Verify: No uncommitted copyright changes\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Codespell Workflow (codespell.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T10.1** Create `codespell.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/codespell.yml`\n  - Name: `Codespell`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T10.2** Define pull_request triggers for codespell.yml\n  - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n  - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n\n- [ ] **T10.3** Create `codespell` job in codespell.yml\n  - Job ID: `codespell`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T10.4** Add checkout step\n  - Use: `actions/checkout@v4`\n  - Verify: Repository checked out\n\n- [ ] **T10.5** Add backup problematic files step\n  - Run: Backup `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at root and nested\n  - Use: `mv` to temporary location\n  - Verify: Files backed up before codespell\n\n- [ ] **T10.6** Add codespell installation step\n  - Run: `pip install codespell`\n  - Verify: codespell installed\n\n- [ ] **T10.7** Add codespell execution step\n  - Run: `codespell --check-filenames --skip '*.min.js,*.lock' --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn .`\n  - Verify: Spelling check runs with correct skip/ignore lists\n\n- [ ] **T10.8** Add restore backed-up files step\n  - Run: Restore backed-up files to original locations\n  - Condition: `if: always()`\n  - Verify: Repository restored to original state\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: Build and Push Release Images (build-push-release.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T11.1** Create `build-push-release.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml`\n  - Name: `Build and Push Release Images`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T11.2** Define push triggers for build-push-release.yml\n  - Trigger: `push` to `main`\n  - Trigger: `push` tags `v*.*.*` and `v*.*.*-*`\n  - Verify: Both branch and tag triggers configured\n\n- [ ] **T11.3** Create `build-and-push` job\n  - Job ID: `build-and-push`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T11.4** Add checkout step (v3)\n  - Use: `actions/checkout@v3`\n  - Verify: Repository checked out\n\n- [ ] **T11.5** Add Go 1.24.4 setup step (v4)\n  - Use: `actions/setup-go@v4` with `go-version: '1.24.4'`\n  - Verify: Go 1.24.4 installed\n\n- [ ] **T11.6** Add Docker Buildx setup step (v2)\n  - Use: `docker/setup-buildx-action@v2`\n  - Verify: Buildx configured\n\n- [ ] **T11.7** Add Docker login to GHCR step\n  - Use: `docker/login-action@v3` with `registry: ghcr.io`, `username: ${{ github.actor }}`, `password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}`\n  - Verify: Authenticated to ghcr.io\n\n- [ ] **T11.8** Add TAG environment variable logic\n  - If `github.ref_type == 'tag'`: `TAG = github.ref_name`\n  - Else: `TAG = latest`\n  - Run: Shell logic to set TAG\n  - Verify: Correct tag selected based on ref type\n\n- [ ] **T11.9** Add workload manager buildx push step\n  - Run: `make docker-buildx-push` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n  - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n\n- [ ] **T11.10** Add router buildx push step\n  - Run: `make docker-buildx-push-router` with same IMAGE_REGISTRY\n  - Verify: Router image built and pushed\n\n- [ ] **T11.11** Add picod buildx push step\n  - Run: `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with same IMAGE_REGISTRY\n  - Verify: Picod image built and pushed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 12: Dify Plugin Publish (dify-plugin-publish.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T12.1** Create `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml`\n  - Name: `Dify Plugin Publish`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T12.2** Define push tag triggers for dify-plugin-publish.yml\n  - Trigger: `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*`\n  - Verify: Tag pattern configured\n\n- [ ] **T12.3** Create `publish` job in dify-plugin-publish.yml\n  - Job ID: `publish`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T12.4** Add dify-plugin CLI download step\n  - Run: Download `dify-plugin` CLI v0.0.6 from GitHub releases\n  - Verify: CLI binary installed\n\n- [ ] **T12.5** Add yq installation step\n  - Run: Install `yq` for YAML processing\n  - Verify: yq available\n\n- [ ] **T12.6** Add manifest.yaml parsing step\n  - Run: Extract plugin metadata using yq\n  - Verify: Plugin name/version extracted\n\n- [ ] **T12.7** Add plugin packaging step\n  - Run: `dify-plugin package` to create plugin bundle\n  - Verify: Plugin packaged successfully\n\n- [ ] **T12.8** Add author repository checkout step\n  - Use: `actions/checkout@v4` with `repository: author/dify-plugins`, `token: ${{ secrets.PLUGIN_ACTION }}`\n  - Verify: Author repository checked out\n\n- [ ] **T12.9** Add plugin file move step\n  - Run: Move `.difypkg` file to correct location\n  - Verify: Plugin file in place\n\n- [ ] **T12.10** Add git branch, commit, push step\n  - Run: Create branch, commit changes, push to author repo\n  - Verify: Changes committed and pushed\n\n- [ ] **T12.11** Add PR creation step\n  - Run: `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` with `GH_TOKEN`\n  - Use: `github/gh-cli` or similar\n  - Verify: Pull request created for plugin submission\n\n---\n\n## Phase 13: Workflow Approval (workflows-approve.yml)\n\n- [ ] **T13.1** Create `workflows-approve.yml` workflow file\n  - File: `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml`\n  - Name: `Approve Workflows`\n  - Verify: Workflow file created\n\n- [ ] **T13.2** Define pull_request_target triggers\n  - Trigger: `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` to `main`, `release-**`\n  - Verify: Correct event types and branches configured\n\n- [ ] **T13.3** Create `approve` job in workflows-approve.yml\n  - Job ID: `approve`\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n  - Verify: Job defined\n\n- [ ] **T13.4** Add GitHub script step for contributor check\n  - Use: `actions/github-script@v7`\n  - Script: List contributor PRs to determine if first-time\n  - Verify: First-time contributor status determined\n\n- [ ] **T13.5** Add ok-to-test label check logic\n  - Script: Check if PR has `ok-to-test` label\n  - Verify: Label presence detected\n\n- [ ] **T13.6** Add conditional workflow run approval\n  - Condition: If NOT first-time OR has `ok-to-test` label\n  - Script: List workflow runs for head SHA with `status: action_required`\n  - Use: `github.rest.actions.approveWorkflowRun()` for each\n  - Verify: Pending workflow runs approved\n\n---\n\n## Phase 14: Workflow Testing & Validation\n\n- [ ] **T14.1** Test main.yml workflow locally with act\n  - Command: `act pull_request -j build` (if act available)\n  - Verify: Workflow syntax valid\n\n- [ ] **T14.2** Validate all workflow YAML syntax\n  - Run: `yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml` or similar\n  - Verify: All workflows pass YAML linting\n\n- [ ] **T14.3** Test path filters with sample PR\n  - Create test PR with Go file changes\n  - Verify: lint.yml triggers correctly\n\n- [ ] **T14.4** Test path filters with Python changes\n  - Create test PR with sdk-python changes\n  - Verify: python-sdk-tests.yml and python-lint.yml trigger\n\n- [ ] **T14.5** Test codespell workflow\n  - Introduce intentional typo in source file\n  - Verify: codespell.yml fails on PR\n\n- [ ] **T14.6** Test build-push-release.yml with test tag\n  - Push test tag `v9.9.9-test`\n  - Verify: Images built and pushed to GHCR\n\n- [ ] **T14.7** Verify Codecov integration\n  - Run test-coverage.yml on PR\n  - Verify: Coverage report uploads (if token configured)\n\n- [ ] **T14.8** Test e2e.yml workflow\n  - Create PR to main\n  - Verify: E2E tests run in Kind cluster\n  - Verify: Logs uploaded on failure\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ All 12 workflow files created in `.github/workflows/`\n2. ✅ `main.yml` builds Workload Manager Docker image on PR\n3. ✅ `e2e.yml` runs E2E tests with Kind v0.30.0, captures logs\n4. ✅ `lint.yml` runs golangci-lint only when Go code changes\n5. ✅ `python-sdk-tests.yml` runs pytest on SDK changes\n6. ✅ `python-lint.yml` runs Ruff from repo root on Python changes\n7. ✅ `test-coverage.yml` runs coverage tests, uploads to Codecov\n8. ✅ `codegen-check.yml` verifies generated code is up to date\n9. ✅ `copyright-check.yml` ensures copyright headers are consistent\n10. ✅ `codespell.yml` checks spelling with proper skip/ignore lists\n11. ✅ `build-push-release.yml` publishes multi-arch images on tags\n12. ✅ `dify-plugin-publish.yml` packages and submits Dify plugin\n13. ✅ `workflows-approve.yml` auto-approves workflows for repeat contributors\n14. ✅ All workflows use correct path filters via dorny/paths-filter\n15. ✅ All workflows have proper conditional execution based on path changes\n16. ✅ Release workflow uses correct action versions (v3/v4/v2 for compatibility)\n17. ✅ E2E workflow captures and uploads failure artifacts\n18. ✅ Coverage workflow supports workflow_call with optional token\n19. ✅ All workflow names match specification\n20. ✅ All triggers target correct branches (main, release-*)\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (all 12 GitHub Actions workflows created)\n- Workflows cover: CI build, E2E, lint (Go/Python), SDK tests, coverage, codegen, copyright, codespell, release publishing, Dify plugin, workflow approval\n- Path filtering via `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for efficient conditional execution\n- E2E uses Kind with `install_only: true` to avoid double cluster creation\n- Release workflow publishes multi-arch images to GHCR\n- First-time contributor workflow approval prevents abuse while enabling CI\n\n(End of file)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775883587724,"end":1775883587735}}}}
